Connecticut Water Service Inc. (CTWS) , the
largest publicly traded water provider in the U.S. Northeast,
today reported second-quarter profit rose 3.6 percent to $4.3
million. Revenue was almost unchanged from a year earlier.  Shares of the Clinton, Connecticut-based company that
supplies drinking water to about 400,000 people have declined
4.6 percent the past year compared with a 13 percent gain by the
biggest water company in the U.S., American Water Works Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
